Map the submitted jurisdiction name to one of the canonical forms above. Accept common abbreviations, state postal codes, and minor punctuation / spacing variants listed next to each entry.

Important scope choices:
- The **District of Columbia** entry is the DC adult-guardianship framework. Statewide Virginia or Maryland material does not canonify to DC.
- State-level entries (e.g. **Alaska**, **Maryland**, **California**, **New York**) carry the statewide adult-guardianship framework for that state.
- County-level entries - **Maricopa County, Arizona**, **Ada County, Idaho**, **Los Angeles County, California**, **Cook County, Illinois**, **Multnomah County, Oregon**, **San Francisco County, California** - are county-scoped. Statewide material from the parent state can support statewide adult-guardianship rules that apply in the county, but county public-guardian / public-fiduciary arrangements need county-scoped evidence.
- A statewide entry and a county entry within the same parent state are distinct canon members (e.g. **California** and **Los Angeles County, California** are separate; both can appear in the same panel). Statewide California material does not canonify to **Los Angeles County, California**.
